race.description: Tab Same Race Multi Mdn Plate
race.comment: BRUTAL ADVANCE (1) switched from a Gold Coast yard and was beaten 1L here first-up. It was a big effort after being bumped on jumping and the speedy galloper can race forward today from an inside gate. Presents fitter and will prove tough to beat. SHAFT ATTACK (3) deserves to break through. He didn't do a bad job at Canberra in stronger last start and just missed there the one prior. Went close at her only start at her home track. Races forward and can make the finish again. SPEED OF THOUGHT (7) resumes and runs along. She went close at Albury two back and Cahill is a key jockey engagement. Maps well and is likely to return further improved. WE SHALL OVERCOME (8) resumes for a Canberra yard and has shown enough to suggest she can be around the mark.
